[2026-03-12T15:55:48Z] [llm] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01GPQAkeQiyTHoLXuE7BrLCU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01BfN24t2ukjRJ86LLSErXp4","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/CLAUDE.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2899,"cache_read_input_tokens":14049,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2899,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0165mefFg1Fyf6LaLScEQMXV","session_id":"b681cdd1-b2f2-4224-b489-8b848ed1cf19","uuid":"73056d7a-29d9-48c6-ad39-f1a7c108cc68"}
[2026-03-12T15:55:48Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BfN24t2ukjRJ86LLSErXp4","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# CLAUDE.md\n     2→\n     3→This file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.\n     4→\n     5→## Project Overview\n     6→\n     7→Cloche is a system for grow-coding high quality applications. It provides containerized\n     8→environments for coding agents, a workflow DSL for linking agentic and script-driven\n     9→tasks, validated code pipelines, and self-evolving tooling.\n    10→\n    11→**Language:** Go\n    12→\n    13→**Full design:** `docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`\n    14→\n    15→## Architecture\n    16→\n    17→Three binaries from one Go module:\n    18→\n    19→- **`cloche`** (CLI) — Short-lived client. Talks to daemon over gRPC. Subcommands: `run`, `status`, `logs`, `stop`.\n    20→- **`cloched`** (Daemon) — Long-running. Manages container lifecycle, collects status, persists state. Executes host workflows (`host.cloche`) step by step on the host machine, dispatching container workflow runs as needed.\n    21→- **`cloche-agent`** (In-Container) — Autonomous. Parses workflow DSL, walks the graph, executes steps, streams status back to daemon. Runs to completion without human intervention.\n    22→\n    23→Hexagonal architecture: domain logic is independent of infrastructure. Ports define\n    24→interfaces (ContainerRuntime, RunStore, CaptureStore, AgentAdapter). Adapters implement\n    25→them (Docker, SQLite, gRPC, Claude Code).\n    26→\n    27→```\n    28→cmd/\n    29→  cloche/           # CLI client\n    30→  cloched/          # Daemon\n    31→  cloche-agent/     # In-container entrypoint\n    32→internal/\n    33→  domain/           # Core types (Workflow, Step, Result, Run)\n    34→  ports/            # Interfaces (store, container, agent, notifier)\n    35→  adapters/         # Implementations (docker, sqlite, grpc, agents)\n    36→  host/             # Host workflow executor (runs steps on host machine)\n    37→```\n    38→\n    39→## Workflow DSL\n    40→\n    41→Steps report named results; wiring maps results to next steps. `done` and `abort` are\n    42→built-in terminals. See `docs/workflows.md` for syntax and semantics.\n    43→\n    44→## Project Layout\n    45→\n    46→Cloche-specific files live in `.cloche/` at the project root:\n    47→\n    48→```\n    49→my-project/\n    50→├── .cloche/\n    51→│   ├── develop.cloche      # Container workflow definition\n    52→│   ├── host.cloche          # Host orchestration workflow (runs on host)\n    53→│   ├── Dockerfile           # Container image\n    54→│   ├── prompts/             # Prompt templates for agent steps\n    55→│   ├── scripts/             # Host-side scripts (e.g. prepare-prompt.sh)\n    56→│   ├── overrides/           # Files copied on top of /workspace/ in container\n    57→│   └── <run-id>/            # Runtime state (gitignored)\n    58→├── src/                     # Existing project source (untouched)\n    59→└── CLAUDE.md\n    60→```\n    61→\n    62→## Container Model\n    63→\n    64→One container per workflow run (not per step). The entire project root is copied into the\n    65→container at `/workspace/`, then override files from `.cloche/overrides/` are applied on\n    66→top. Results are extracted to git branches. Network is allowlisted.\n    67→\n    68→## Agent Support\n    69→\n    70→Agent-agnostic. The `AgentAdapter` interface wraps any coding agent. Initial adapters:\n    71→Generic (arbitrary commands) and Claude Code.\n    72→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0165mefFg1Fyf6LaLScEQMXV","session_id":"b681cdd1-b2f2-4224-b489-8b848ed1cf19","uuid":"dbfaa8ef-b71b-4a81-9ccf-ea3b8589453c"}
